pooled gut DNA from three female monarchs
There are two Biological OsmoSampler samples, each comprised of approximately 10 mL river water filtered onto PES.

The guts of 60 female adults were then dissected on a plate containing 2 ml sterile phosphate-buffered solution (10 mmol/liter, pH 7.4, Ambion, Thermo Fisher Scientific, Madison, WI) using a pair of sterilized entomological forceps (flame-sterilized) under a stereomicroscope (Leica MZ16, 1.6X). The extracted guts were deposited in plastic Eppendorf 1.5 ml tubes containing DNA shield and stored at -70C for DNA extraction and sequencing.

Soil covered roots were then placed in a sterile flask with 50 ml of sterilized phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) solution and shaken gently to wash soil from the roots. Sterile forceps were then used to remove any roots remaining in the soil slurry solution.
Sample was transportered immediately to the library. Total DNA was extracted and sent for sequencing
